solution.p:
To compute the exact value, we use the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus. Antidifferentiating r(t) = 0.0069t^3 -0.125t^2+11.079, we find that

        \int_4^{10} 0.0069t^3 -0.125t^2+11.079 \, dt =\mathstrut \amp  \left. 0.0069 \cdot \frac{1}{4} \, t^4 - 0.125 \cdot \frac{1}{3} t^3 + 11.079t \right|_4^{10}
        \approx\mathstrut \amp  44.282.
